1️⃣ What is a Transaction?
Simple Idea

A Transaction is a group of SQL operations executed as a single unit

👉 Either ALL succeed or NONE happen

Real-World Mental Model 🧠

Think about bank transfer:

👉 Transfer ₹1000 from A → B

Steps:

Deduct ₹1000 from A
Add ₹1000 to B
Problem ❌

If system crashes after step 1:

A loses money ❌
B doesn't receive ❌

👉 Data becomes inconsistent

Solution → Transaction ✅
Either:
✔ Both steps succeed
OR
❌ Both fail (no change)
Memory Trick 🧠
Transaction = All or Nothing
ACID Properties (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)

These ensure transactions are safe and reliable

1. Atomicity (All or Nothing)

👉 Either complete fully OR not at all

Example:

Money transfer should not be half-done
2. Consistency (Valid State)

👉 Database must remain correct

Example:

Total money should remain same
3. Isolation (No Interference)

👉 Multiple transactions don’t disturb each other

Example:

Two users withdrawing should not clash
4. Durability (Permanent Save)

👉 Once committed → data is permanent

Even after crash ✅

Easy Way to Remember 🧠
ACID = Safety Rules of Database
Python Connection

Think:

try:
    deduct_money()
    add_money()
except:
    rollback()

👉 Same concept as transaction

2️⃣ COMMIT & ROLLBACK
Simple Idea

These control saving or undoing changes

COMMIT

👉 Saves changes permanently

COMMIT;
ROLLBACK

👉 Undo changes

ROLLBACK;
Example
BEGIN;

UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance - 1000 WHERE id=1;
UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance + 1000 WHERE id=2;

COMMIT;
If Error Happens
ROLLBACK;

👉 Everything goes back to original state

Python Connection 🧠
backup = data.copy()

try:
    update_data()
except:
    data = backup

👉 ROLLBACK = restore backup

Why This is Important

✔ Used in banking apps
✔ Used in payment systems
✔ Prevents data corruption
✔ Ensures reliability

